<% content_for :title, "CurrentScope Showcase" %>

<section class="lobby">
  <h1>The harbor master's ledger</h1>

  <p>
    You are browsing as <b>Visitor</b> — a role-less account that, fail-closed,
    can reach almost nothing. That is the point: step into a seeded persona and
    watch the very same screens re-render for <em>their</em> permissions. The
    engine reads one ambient subject, so the list, the gate, and the buttons can
    never disagree.
  </p>

  <p>
    Pick a persona to act as. A banner keeps naming both identities — who you are
    acting as, and who you really are — until you stop.
  </p>

  <%= render "layouts/persona_switcher" %>
</section>
